-- U.S. Is Concerned That Piracy Off Nigerian Coast May Be Increasing
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-12-16T13:44:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-16/u-s-is-concerned-that-piracy-off-nigerian-coast-may-be-increasing.html
The U.S. is concerned piracy may be
on the increase off the oil-rich coast of Nigeria, U.S. Counter-
Piracy Coordinator Donna Hopkins said on a conference call
today.  Somali pirates off the Horn of Africa have received at
least $100 million in ransom over the past two years, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
